    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is the scan painful?",
        "answer": "No. You only feel the table moving and hear rhythmic knocking. \n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How soon can I resume normal activities?",
        "answer": "Immediately—no recovery time needed. \n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I undergo MRI if I have dental implants?",
        "answer": "Most titanium implants are safe; inform the technologist for verification. \n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Will I need a follow-up contrast study?",
        "answer": "Only if the non-contrast images are inconclusive or a tiny abnormality is suspected. \n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Why is an MRI scan of brain blood vessels without contrast dye important?",
        "answer": " The without contrast aspect is important because it means the images of your brain blood vessels are obtained without injecting any special dye (contrast medium). This makes the MRI scan brain blood vessels without dye an excellent option for patients who may have allergies to contrast media, have impaired kidney function, or simply wish to avoid any unnecessary substances. It provides valuable diagnostic information with an enhanced safety profile."
      },
